This whole tungsten thing is a new thing for me this year, Iâ€™ve tried with whole minnows, minnow head and plastics, to be honest theyâ€™re like any other bait I use, sometimes theyâ€™ll munch a Smokey on a rope and some days doesnâ€™t matter what you throw at them, theyâ€™re being picky.

About 55 years or so ago I had a black crappie in the freezer that was quite big that I caught at Stokes Bay I was going to have mounted. It was cold this one day so I though I'd defrost the freezer. I put everything outside in the baskets. Upon bringing every thingÂ  in the house and back into the freezer I noticed my black crappie was missing. It had to be my German Shepard, He never touched the beef or anything else just the crappie. I think he was ticked off at me because we hadn't been fishing for a spell as I seldom went without him. We never did see it again, not even the bag it was in Haha. I've never caught another that big. Happy Days.
